'''Kirchstetten''' is a town in district of [[Sankt Pölten-Land]] in the [[Austria]]n state of [[Lower Austria]].
==Population== {{Historical populations |align=left |1971|1358 |1981|1451 |1991|1617 |2001|1814 }} {{clear left}}
==Personalities== It was the home during part of their lives to the Austrian poet [[Josef Weinheber]] and the English poet [[W. H. Auden]]. Auden is buried in a Kirchstetten churchyard<ref>http://www.poetsgraves.co.uk/auden.htm</ref> and his home, at Hinterholz 6, houses a small [[writer's home museum]] to the poet in his loft study.<ref>http://www.noemuseen.at/de/?tt=MUSEUM_R8&id=85953&ci=museum&oid=219</ref>
