{{Infobox person | name = Matthew Christopher | image = Fashion Designer Matthew Christopher, mc2016.jpg | caption = Matthew Christopher on left, 2016 | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1976|3|16|mf=yes}} | birth_place = [[Packwood, Iowa]] | occupation = [[Fashion designer]] | education = [[Art Institute of Chicago]]{{br}}[[Iowa State University]] | spouse = David J. Marchi (married 2012)}} '''Matthew Christopher Sobaski''' is an American fashion designer mostly known for bridal wear. He is the owner and the CEO of a [[Haute couture|couture]] [[fashion house]] in [[New York City]].
== Personal life ==
Christopher was born on March 16, 1976, in [[Packwood, Iowa|Packwood]], [[Iowa]] to Kenneth Sobaski, a hog farmer and Sandy Sobaski, a registered nurse. Christopher learned to sew participating in [[4-H]].<ref name="nypost">{{cite news|last1=Aktar|first1=Alev|title=Iowa-born designer Matthew Christopher grows a hit NYC bridal line|url=https://nypost.com/2014/10/08/iowa-born-designer-matthew-christopher-grows-a-hit-nyc-bridal-line/|accessdate=February 1, 2016|work=New York Post|date=October 8, 2014}}</ref> He attended the [[Art Institute of Chicago]] for one year before completing his studies at [[Iowa State University]].<ref name=iastate>{{cite news | url=http://www.news.iastate.edu/news/2011/mar/MatthewChristopher | title=Matthew Christopher Inc | work=[[Iowa State University]] | date=30 March 2011 | accessdate=31 January 2016}}</ref> He moved to New York City in 2000 to pursue a career in the field of couture designing.{{citation needed|date=February 2016}} This is where he met his future partner, contemporary artist, David J. Marchi. The two were joined in 2012.<ref name="Married">{{cite news | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/12/30/fashion/weddings/matthew-sobaski-david-marchi-weddings.html | title=Matthew Sobaski David Marchi Wedding | work=[[The New York Times]] | date=30 December 2012 | accessdate=31 January 2016}}</ref>
== In popular culture ==
Christopher's designs for gowns are featured in movies including ''[[The Wedding Ringer]]'' with [[Kaley Cuoco]].<ref name="Kaley Cuoco">{{cite news | url=http://www.brides.com/blogs/aisle-say/2015/01/the-wedding-ringer-wedding-dress-contest-kaley-cuoco-sweeting.html | title=Kaley Cuoco wore Matthew's designer gown on The Wedding Ringer | work=[[Brides (magazine)|Brides]] | date=15 January 2015 | accessdate=31 January 2016}}</ref> Christopher's list of clientele includes [[Kristin Chenoweth]],<ref name=nypost/> [[Carli Lloyd]],<ref name="Carli Lloyd">{{cite news | url=https://www.theknot.com/content/carli-llyod-matthew-christopher-espy-awards | title=Matthew Christopher designs for Carli Lloyd's ESPY Dress | work=[[XO Group|theknot.com]] | date=30 March 2011 | accessdate=31 January 2016}}</ref> [[Julie Lake]],<ref name="Julie Lake">{{cite news | url=https://www.theknot.com/content/julie-lake-orange-is-the-new-black-wedding-plans | title=Matthew's work with 'Orange is the new Black' star, Julie Lake | work=[[XO Group|theknot.com]] | date=1 January 2012 | accessdate=31 January 2016}}</ref> and [[Debra Messing]].<ref name=nypost/> Several of Christopher's couture gowns and wedding dresses were covered in the January 2016 edition of ''Vanity Fair'' in a featured article. He makes a cameo in the documentary ''He Lied About Everything'' as the custome designer of [[Benita Alexander]]'s dress.<ref name="Vanity Fair">{{cite news | url=http://www.vanityfair.com/news/2016/01/celebrity-surgeon-nbc-news-producer-scam | title=Matthew Christopher's work appeared on Vanity Fair | work=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]] | date=31 January 2016 | accessdate=31 January 2016}}</ref> His gowns have also appeared in the Broadway adaptation of ''[[Honeymoon in Vegas#Stage version|Honeymoon in Vegas]]''<ref name="Honeymoon In Vegas">{{cite news|title=BWW Exclusive: Designer Matthew Christopher Shows Off the Wedding Wardrobe of HONEYMOON IN VEGAS!|url=http://www.broadwayworld.com/article/BWW-Exclusive-Designer-Matthew-Christopher-Shows-Off-the-Wedding-Wardrobe-of-HONEYMOON-IN-VEGAS-20150112|accessdate=February 1, 2016|work=Broadway World|date=January 12, 2015}}</ref> and on the TV show ''[[Say Yes to the Dress]]''.<ref name="Say Yes To The Dress">{{cite news | url=http://www.people.com/article/brittney-griner-glory-johnson-say-yes-to-the-dress | title=Matthew Christopher's work featured on Say Yes To Dress | work=[[people.com]] | date=30 January 2015 | accessdate=31 January 2016}}</ref>
